p conglomerate, the book examines how managers attempt to perfect corporate social life through new office programs while also minimizing the risks of creating new hierarchies. Ultimately, this book reveals how office life is a battleground for working out the promises and the perils of economic democratization in one of East Asia's most dynamic countries.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aCorporationszKorea (South)xEmployees. 0aHierarchieszKorea (South) 0aHierarchieszKorea (South). 0aPersonnel managementzKorea (South) 0aPersonnel managementzKorea (South). 0aQuality of work lifezKorea (South) 0aQuality of work lifezKorea (South). 0aWhite collar workerszKorea (South) 0aWhite collar workerszKorea (South). 0aWork environmentzKorea (South) 0aWork environmentzKorea (South). 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Human Services.2bisacsh  aSouth Korea.  acorporations.  adistinction.  ahierarchy.  amanagement.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076648640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150363188540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503631885423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503631885/original  a978-3-11-076648-6  Stanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles